ty is a notable drawback, the same candidate also generates a positive crew atmosphere and is fully reliable\u2014attributes that can be reinforced through crew\u2011resource\u2011training and clear procedural checklists.\nCandidates\u202fA and\u202fB each bring valuable technical or leadership strengths, but their organizational or interpersonal weaknesses could more directly jeopardize the sustained coordination required on long routes. Candidate\u202fD\u2019s problem\u2011solving is strong, yet his weak leadership and arrogance pose a risk to crew cohesion, which is essential for extended flights.\nGiven the current evidence, **Candidate\u202fC** remains the best overall fit for the long\u2011distance pilot position, provided the airline implements targeted communication training and monitoring to mitigate his noted weakness.\nIf any participant possesses concrete crew\u2011feedback or performance data that would alter this balance\u2014particularly regarding Candidate\u202fC\u2019s communication effectiveness or any hidden teamwork strengths for Candidates\u202fA,\u202fB, or\u202fD\u2014please share it now.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We are agent_1. We have just received from agent_2 (via tool) that they have no additional info beyond listed attributes. Now we need to produce our public contribution and vote. We need to incorporate this new info: agent_2 confirms no extra info. So we still have same knowledge. We need to continue discussion: maybe ask agent_3 for any extra info? But we already asked agent_3 earlier and they responded with no extra info. So all agents have no extra info beyond listed attributes. So we have to make a decision based on existing data. We can now finalize vote. All agents currently leaning Candidate C. We should state reasoning, note uncertainties, maybe ask if any other agent has any other info? But we have asked both and they said no. So we can finalize.\n\nThus public message: summarize that we have no further info, reaffirm evaluation, note that Candidate C remains best despite communication issues, but we could suggest mitigation like crew resource training. Vote Candidate C.\n\nProceed."}
